title: UPS cargo plane crash kills 12 after engine failure | 7NEWS
description: UPS flight 2976 crashed shortly after takeoff from Louisville Airport in Kentucky, killing 12 people including three crew members and nine people on the ground. The 34-year-old cargo plane had recently undergone six weeks of maintenance for a fuel tank crack, and the crew was switched to this aircraft at the last minute due to maintenance issues with their originally assigned plane. Investigators are examining the black box data and maintenance records to determine what caused the number one engine to catch fire and fall off during takeoff. title: Deadly typhoon Kalmagi strikes Vietnam after Philippines devastation | 7NEWS
description: Typhoon Kalmagi, the deadliest typhoon of the year, has made landfall in Vietnam after devastating the Philippines and killing at least 114 people. Vietnamese officials have evacuated over half a million people and deployed 260,000 soldiers as the country faces winds up to 150 kilometres per hour and sea surges as high as 10 metres. The storm particularly impacted Cebu, the Philippines' most populous island, where flooding from the swollen Mananga River consumed entire cities and displaced 560,000 people. title: Thieves steal war memorial plaques on Gold Coast | 7NEWS
description: Thieves have stolen bronze plaques from multiple war memorials on the Gold Coast, including commemorative plaques honouring Korean War veterans, Kokoda track fighters, and Papua New Guinean soldiers who fought alongside Australian and New Zealand forces in World War II. Police allege two men, aged 40 and 47, took the plaques to a scrap metal yard, with one stolen plaque weighing approximately 40 kilograms. The incident has devastated the local RSL sub-branch and occurred just ahead of Remembrance Day. title: Cross-border hit squad hunted for Melbourne gangster murder | 7NEWS
description: Detectives are investigating the murder of 21-year-old Athan Borsinos, who was shot dead in a Wollert laneway on July 31st as he prepared to attend Heidelberg Magistrates Court. Police believe the killing was carried out by hired assassins from a New South Wales crime syndicate who travelled to Melbourne specifically for the targeted hit. Security footage from an Epping shopping centre shows two suspects believed to be the shooters, who fled in a Nissan Patrol that was later found burnt out. title: Shirley Valentine star Pauline Collins dies aged 85 | 7NEWS
description: Award-winning British actress Pauline Collins has died peacefully at her home in north London at the age of 85. Collins became internationally famous for playing the title character in Shirley Valentine, both on stage and screen, a role about a bored housewife's journey of self-discovery that struck a chord with disillusioned women worldwide. She won an Olivier Award for the West End production, a Tony Award on Broadway, a BAFTA for the film adaptation, and received an Oscar nomination, having previously been known for the 1970s drama series Upstairs, Downstairs.
